INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,173,265,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">This MDRC report examines the experiences of three colleges currently involved in Achieving the Dream and their efforts to improve instruction in developmental education classrooms.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','page',0,176,268,'und',0,'<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">One Goal &ndash; Success For ALL Community College Students:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">Achieving the Dream seeks to help more students earn postsecondary credentials, including occupational certificates and degrees. Since community college students often take several years to earn certificates or degrees, Achieving the Dream works with institutions to improve student progression through intermediate milestones. </span></p><p style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">These indicators include the rates at which students: </span></p><ol><li style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: white; \"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">Successfully complete remedial or developmental instruction and advance to credit-bearing courses</span></li><li style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: white; \"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">Enroll in and successfully complete the initial college-level or gatekeeper courses in subjects such as math and English</span></li><li style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: white; \"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">Complete the courses they take with a grade of &quot;C&quot; or better</span></li><li style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: white; \"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">Persistence from one term to the next</span></li><li style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: white; \"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; \">Attain a credential</span></li></ol>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,177,2594,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream colleges engage in a process of institutional improvement to increase student success. A central component of this process is engaging internal and external stakeholders to help develop and implement interventions or changes in programs and services that improve student success. To determine whether these interventions do indeed improve student outcomes, and what changes and refinements should be made to produce further improvements, colleges need to evaluate their interventions</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,178,271,'und',0,'<p>This guide is Achieving the Dream&rsquo;s most comprehensive overview of the signature framework for helping more students finish the courses they start, persist from one term to the next, and earn a certificate or associate degree. The Field Guide includes an in-depth overview of Achieving the Dream&rsquo;s four principles and five-step process, case studies, and a readiness assessment for prospective colleges to determine how their policies are practices measure up.</p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','page',0,180,273,'und',0,'<p>Every Achieving the Dream Institution develops and implements research-based policies and practices based on quantitative and qualitative analyses of its institutional strengths, problem areas, and achievement gaps. The colleges are committed to assessing the effectiveness of their policies and practices, institutionalizing approaches that prove successful, and sharing their findings widely.</p><p>In 2010-11, Achieving the Dream Leader Colleges pioneered several promising policies and practices to help more students succeed. It is important to keep in mind that these interventions are a part of Achieving the Dream&#39;s larger student-centered model of institutional improvement, and any attempt to replicate a promising practice should be done in the context of Achieving the Dream&#39;s integrated framework.</p><p>Learn more:</p><ul><li><a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices</a></li><li><a href=\"/resource/2010_promising_practices\">2010 Promising Practices</a></li></ul>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,181,2123,'und',0,'<p>Read the <a href=\"/sites/default/files/resources/2011_promising_practices_full.pdf\">full 2011 Promising Practices report</a>, or choose one of the chapters below. Each chapter addresses one of nine categories:</p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,182,2495,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream and LearningCounts.org launched a new national partnership to remove obstacles and accelerate the pace of adult learners earning college credentials. This evidence-based partnership is poised to deliver more credentialed workers to the American workforce over the next ten years.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,183,300,'und',0,'<p>Senior college leaders actively support efforts to improve student success and are committed to achieving equity in student outcomes across racial, ethnic, and income groups. Administrators, boards of trustees, and faculty and staff leaders demonstrate a willingness to make changes in policies, programs, and resource allocation to improve student success.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Danville Community College, El Paso Community College and Phillips Community College at the University of Arkansas.</p><p>This report is part of our <a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p>','Senior college leaders actively support efforts to improve student success and are committed to achieving equity in student outcomes across racial, ethnic, and income groups. Administrators, boards of trustees, and faculty and staff leaders demonstrate a willingness to make changes in policies, programs, and resource allocation to improve student success. Schools included in this section are: Danville Community College, El Paso Community College and Phillips Community College at the University of Arkansas.','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,184,298,'und',0,'<p>The college establishes processes for using data about student progression and outcomes to identify achievement gaps among student groups, formulates strategies for addressing the gaps identified and improving student success overall, and evaluates the effectiveness of those strategies.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Brazosport College, Tacoma Community College, and Yakima Valley Community College.</p><p>This report is part of our <a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p>','The college establishes processes for using data about student progression and outcomes to identify achievement gaps among student groups, formulates strategies for addressing the gaps identified and improving student success overall, and evaluates the effectiveness of those strategies. Schools included in this section are: Brazosport College, Tacoma Community College, and Yakima Valley Community College.','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,185,284,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream, Inc., a national nonprofit that helps 3.5 million community college students stay in school and earn a college certificate or degree, announced that 23 additional Achieving the Dream Institutions have earned Leader College distinction. These emerging leaders join the ranks of now 52 institutions that have achieved Leader College status by raising persistence and graduation rates, closing achievement gaps, and changing lives. </font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,186,285,'und',0,'<p>We are proud to congratulate Mott Community College, Southwest Texas Junior College, and Valencia Community College for being named three of the ten finalists for The Aspen Prize by the Aspen Institute&rsquo;s College Excellence Program. These three Achieving the Dream Institutions are recognized for their extraordinary efforts and demonstrable improvements in student outcomes, and now enter the last stage of the competition for the $1 million prize.</p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,187,287,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Yesterday, Achieving the Dream, Inc. &ndash; a national nonprofit dedicated to helping more community college students, particularly low-income students and students of color, stay in school and earn a college certificate or degree &ndash; opened the doors to its new headquarters in the greater Washington, D.C. area and welcomed five new staff members. This expansion marks the completion of a successful incubation period which took place over the course of eighteen months to transition Achieving the Dream from a demonstration initiative into a strong, sustainable national nonprofit leading the nation&#39;s largest student success reform network in higher education history. </font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,188,288,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">I congratulate Kay and Byron McClenney on earning the American Association of Community College&rsquo;s Leadership Award. This prestigious award is presented to individuals whose accomplishments and professional contributions to the community college field have been outstanding. Kay and Byron are truly deserving of this recognition, as their hard work and dedication have touched the lives of countless community college students nationwide.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,189,289,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Engaging adjunct faculty in student success reform is a significant challenge for community colleges, and Achieving the Dream &ndash; a national nonprofit dedicated to helping community college students succeed &ndash; is addressing this challenge head-on. Yesterday, Achieving the Dream released a new publication and hosted a national workshop offering community colleges timely, tangible tips for sharpening their focus on faculty engagement. </font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,190,290,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Signifying a strong commitment to student success and completion, thirty community colleges, including the entire Los Angeles District, have joined Achieving the Dream. This is the largest cohort in Achieving the Dream history, and these colleges will begin work immediately to identify strategies for improving student success, closing achievement gaps, and increasing retention, persistence, and completion rates.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,191,291,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream named Mrs. Diane Bastian and Representative Joaquin Castro to the Board of Directors. Bastian &ndash; a successful entrepreneur and community college graduate, and Castro &ndash; a Harvard-trained lawyer and elected official for the state of Texas, will enrich the capacity of the Board to counsel and guide Achieving the Dream in the years ahead.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,192,292,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Using data - concrete evidence on student performance - to improve college programs and services is a founding principle of Achieving the Dream. Since the launch seven years ago, Achieving the Dream has consistently emphasized with colleges the importance of allowing data to stimulate reflection and discussion, and to advance decisions in the quest for better student success outcomes. That is the ATD way, and we hold ourselves to that same standard. Achieving the Dream applauds MDRC and the Community College Research Center for their rigorous research and welcomes the findings in the interim report, Turning the Tide: Five Years of Achieving the Dream in Community Colleges.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,193,3464,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream: Community Colleges Count and Lumina Foundation for Education this evening announced that El Paso Community College (EPCC) has been honored with the third annual Leah Meyer Austin Institutional Student Success Leadership Award. EPCC received the award during the opening of the annual Achieving the Dream Strategy Institute in Indianapolis, IN.&nbsp;</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,194,294,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Despite overall stagnant national community college completion rates, Achieving the Dream Leader Colleges are increasing student success and completion outcomes, particularly from low-income students and students of color.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,195,314,'und',0,'<p>Faculty, student services staff, and administrators share responsibility for student success, and collaborate on assessing the effectiveness of programs and services and improving them. Other stakeholders with influence on student success (K-12 systems, community groups, employers, etc.) are included in discussions about student performance, desired outcomes, and potential improvement strategies. The college also gains valuable insight about ways to improve student success from students themselves through surveys, focus groups, and/or advisory councils.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Bunker Hill Community College, College of the Mainland, El Paso Community College, Northampton Community College, Galveston College, Delaware County Community College, Eastern Gateway Community college, and San Jacinto College.</p><p>This report is part of our <a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p>','Faculty, student services staff, and administrators share responsibility for student success, and collaborate on assessing the effectiveness of programs and services and improving them. Other stakeholders with influence on student success (K-12 systems, community groups, employers, etc.) are included in discussions about student performance, desired outcomes, and potential improvement strategies. The college also gains valuable insight about ways to improve student success from students themselves through surveys, focus groups, and/or advisory councils. Schools included in this section are: Bunker Hill Community College, College of the Mainland, El Paso Community College, Northampton Community College, Galveston College, Delaware County Community College, Eastern Gateway Community College, and San Jacinto College.','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,196,304,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream: Community Colleges Count <font size=\"3\"><font size=\"2\">announced that Carol Lincoln has joined its team as Senior Vice President. Ms. Lincoln has more than 30 years of experience in community college reform and will continue to help ATD transition from a demonstration initiative into a strong, sustainable national nonprofit leading America&rsquo;s community college reform movement.</font></font></font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,197,303,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream announced that it received a significant grant from Lumina Foundation for Education to bolster its work in bringing student success strategies to more institutions around the country.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,198,302,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream announced that seven community colleges have emerged as leaders in the national student completion movement.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,199,305,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream is adding 26 colleges from seven states and the District of Columbia in 2010, expanding its network of institutions to more than 130 institutions in 24 states and the District of Columbia and now reaching more than one million students.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,200,315,'und',0,'<p>The college establishes planning processes that rely on data to set goals for student success and then uses the data to measure goal attainment. The college regularly evaluates its academic programs and services to determine how well they promote student success and how they can be improved. Decisions about budget allocations are based on evidence of program effectiveness and are linked to plans to increase student success. Faculty and staff are afforded professional development opportunities that reinforce efforts that help to close achievement gaps and improve overall student success.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Community College of Allegheny County, Durham Technical Community College, Guilford Technical Community College, Northern Virginia Community College and Hillsborough Community College.&nbsp;</p><p>This report is part of our&nbsp;<a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p>','The college establishes planning processes that rely on data to set goals for student success and then uses the data to measure goal attainment. The college regularly evaluates its academic programs and services to determine how well they promote student success and how they can be improved. Decisions about budget allocations are based on evidence of program effectiveness and are linked to plans to increase student success. Faculty and staff are afforded professional development opportunities that reinforce efforts that help to close achievement gaps and improve overall student success. Schools included in this section are: Community College of Allegheny County, Durham Technical Community College, Guilford Technical Community College, Northern Virginia Community College and Hillsborough Community College. ','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,201,307,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream and Lumina Foundation for Education today announced that Guilford Technical Community College (GTCC) has been honored with the second annual Leah Meyer Austin Institutional Student Success Leadership Award. GTCC received the award during the opening of the annual Achieving the Dream Strategy Institute in Charlotte, NC. <a href=\"http://www.achievingthedream.org/Portal/Modules/a6bc58ab-31f2-44fa-b21e-59b673cf6c26.asset?\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about the 2010 Leah Meyer Austin Institutional Student Success Leadership Award.</a></font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,202,313,'und',0,'<p>Developmental education courses are designed for enrollees who are underprepared for college-level work. These courses are also referred to as college-prep, transitional, and foundational education on some campuses. Colleges generally offer courses in math, reading, and writing. Colleges may offer up to three levels of remediation before students are eligible for college-level coursework.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Aiken Technical College, The Alamo Colleges, Houston Community College, Lee College, Montgomery County Community College, North Central State College, Roxbury Community College, Westmoreland County Community College, Zane State College, and Martin Community College.</p><p>This report is part of our&nbsp;<a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p>','Developmental education courses are designed for enrollees who are underprepared for college-level work. These courses are also referred to as college-prep, transitional, and foundational education on some campuses. Colleges generally offer courses in math, reading, and writing. Colleges may offer up to three levels of remediation before students are eligible for college-level coursework. Schools included in this section are: Aiken Technical College, The Alamo Colleges, Houston Community College, Lee College, Montgomery County Community College, North Central State College, Roxbury Community College, Westmoreland County Community College, Zane State College, and Martin Community College.','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,203,309,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream will host a record number of attendees at its annual Strategy Institute February 2&ndash;5, 2010 in Charlotte, NC.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,204,310,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream announced that twenty-one ATD colleges have earned its newly created Leader College designation by virtue of sustained improvement on key student achievement indicators.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,205,312,'und',0,'<p>First-Year Experience efforts are comprehensive approaches designed to improve success rates and increase retention of first-year students. FYE programs may include interventions focused on the streamlining admissions processes, increasing financial aid uptake, community outreach, student success courses, and targeted orientation and advisement.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Brazosport College, Cuyahoga Community College, Phillips Community College at the University of Arkansas, Southwest Texas Junior College, Tallahassee College, and Pulaski Technical College.&nbsp;</p><p>This report is part of our <a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','First-Year Experience efforts are comprehensive approaches designed to improve success rates and increase retention of first-year students. FYE programs may include interventions focused on the streamlining admissions processes, increasing financial aid uptake, community outreach, student success courses, and targeted orientation and advisement. Schools included in this section are: Brazosport College, Cuyahoga Community College, Phillips Community College at the University of Arkansas, Southwest Texas Junior College, Tallahassee College, and Pulaski Technical College. ','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','press_release',0,206,316,'und',0,'<p><font face=\"Verdana, Helvetica\" size=\"2\">Achieving the Dream announced today that Dr. William Trueheart has been named Chief Executive Officer of the five-year-old initiative.</font></p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','resource',0,207,317,'und',0,'<p>Student success begins in the classroom, so Achieving the Dream Institutions also implement strategies to improve pedagogical practices. Strategies aimed at improving the quality of the learning experience may include interventions targeted to gateway courses, employing active and cooperating learning practices, technology-supported, experiential and service learning activities.</p><p>Schools included in this section are: Bunker Hill Community College, Highline Community College, Orangeburg-Calhoun Technical College, Patrick Henry Community College, Renton Technical College, and Valencia College.</p><p>This report is part of our <a href=\"/resource/2011_promising_practices\">2011 Promising Practices Report (full report)</a>.</p>','Student success begins in the classroom, so Achieving the Dream Institutions also implement strategies to improve pedagogical practices. Strategies aimed at improving the quality of the learning experience may include interventions targeted to gateway courses, employing active and cooperating learning practices, technology-supported, experiential and service learning activities. Schools included in this section are: Bunker Hill Community College, Highline Community College, Orangeburg-Calhoun Technical College, Patrick Henry Community College, Renton Technical College, and Valencia College.','filtered_html');
