INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','hidden_page',0,3185,5932,'und',0,'<p>Achieving the Dream has adopted a visual identity system that bolsters the identification of the network and establishes a sense of consistency in an otherwise complex, crowded, and always-changing field of postsecondary education. The system includes three logos:</p><ol><li><a href=\"/logo_identity_standards/official_logo\">the Official Achieving the Dream, Inc. Logo</a>, which is the signature graphic identity symbol and the cornerstone of the entire identity system</li><li><a href=\"/logo_identity_standards/institution_endorsement\">the Achieving the Dream Institution Endorsement Logo</a>, which all ATD-participating institutions are welcome to adopt and incorporate into existing institutional communications and marketing vehicles; and</li><li><a href=\"/logo_identity_standards/leader_college_mark_of_distinction\">the Leader College Mark of Distinction Logo</a>, which is available only to ATD Leader Colleges, is a mechanism for co-branding with ATD, Inc. and distinguishing an institution for its accomplishments in advancing student success and completion.</li></ol><p>Each logo includes an accompanying guide, which details how to use the different versions of each logo, including information on color, spacing, sizing, applications, and typefaces to help you make best use of our look. Scroll down for more information and to download the guides and the logos. For additional questions, contact Achieving the Dream Assistant Director of Communications Lauren Lewis at 240-450-0075 ext 317 or <a href=\"/contact\">by email</a>.</p>','','filtered_html');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','hidden_page',0,3186,5936,'und',0,'<p>The Leader College Mark of Distinction Logo is available only to ATD Leader Colleges, and is a clean and simple way to distinguish your institution as a leader among peers in this national push for student success and completion. Your first step should be to download the Leader College Mark of Distinction Usage Guide, which references rules regarding the use of this logo.</p><p><a href=\"/sites/default/files/achieving_the_dream_leader_college_mark_guidelines.pdf\">Download the Leader College Mark of Distinction Usage Guide</a>.</p><p><a href=\"/sites/default/files/achieving_the_dream_leader_college_affiliation_statement_guidelines.pdf\">Download the Leader College Affiliation Statement Usage Guidelines</a>.</p><h3><img alt=\"\" class=\"image-inline_photo_float_right\" src=\"http://achievingthedream.org/sites/default/files/styles/inline_photo_float_right/public/images/ATD-LCMark-3272KSolid.png\" title=\"\" />Signature</h3><ul><li><a href=\"/sites/default/files/ATD-LCMark-3272KSolid.eps\">Download this as an EPS file</a>. EPS files are a standard format for graphics professionals and those more familiar with publishing. This format allows for quality usage at any size enlargement.</li><li><a href=\"/sites/default/files/images/ATD-LCMark-3272KSolid.png\">Download this as a PNG file</a>. PNG is a standard cross-platform (Mac or PC) format that can be used on the Web.</li><li><a href=\"/sites/default/files/images/ATD-LCMark-3272KSolid.jpg\">Download this as a JPEG file</a>. Please note that JPEG files cannot be significantly enlarged beyond the original signature size contained within these original files. These JPEGs are 72 dpi.</li></ul>','','filtered_html');
