INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3792,8864,'und',0,'To address concerns over gateway English completion rates and adapt to new state-mandated cutoff scores for gateway English, the English Department has developed a multi-pronged placement and instructional strategy. (1) The Intensive Writing Refresher is a free 12-hour refresher of key elements of the capstone WRT 116 course, followed by a retest on COMPASS. (2) The paired course allows students to take WRT 116 and ENG 101 in the same term. (3) The ENG 101 lab course is for students who fall into the margin between the collegeÕs former COMPASS writing cutoff and the new state standard (11 points), AND who score a 5 or above on a secondary COMPASS eWrite test. The lab provides for an additional hour of individualized instruction right before or after the standard class.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3793,8865,'und',0,'COLS150 Applied Skills for Academic Success was designed to close performance gaps.  As of Fall 2009, COLS150 is required for students who need both ENGL026 Writing Skills II & READ017 Critical Reading, before taking ENGL101 English I.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3794,8866,'und',0,'The adoption of the Accelerated Learning Program from Community College of Baltimore County.  Students co-enroll in the upper level, of two levels, of developmental writing and English I.  The concern addressed is the leaky pipeline of developmental education in which students become demotivated and stop-out or drop-out.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3795,8867,'und',0,'All students requiring two or more developmental courses due to scores on the placement test will also be required to take the student success course.\n\n\n\n*Includes all FT/PT FTIC degree-seeking students enrolled in College Success Strategies during the fall term (as counted at Week 3 of the semester).\n\n',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3796,8891,'und',0,'All students taking developmental math and writing will be required to take the same end of course exam to gage readiness to enter college math/English classes.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3797,8892,'und',0,'MyWritingLab is being incorporated into English redesign implemented Fall 2011.  Students complete a diagnostic which populates their individualized study plans. They progress through the course at their own pace, asking for instructor assistance as needed. It permits acceleration through a course, so that students may move quickly through any sequence. Students may access the program from any computer that has internet capabilities.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3798,8893,'und',0,'The college is in the implementation stage of revising the developmental reading and writing programs to incorporate CAI (MyWritingLab and MyFoundationsLab) as a required component of these courses based on the success of the CAI intervention in math.  In addition, the emotional intelligence intervention is being incorporated into the two levels of developmental writing.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3799,8894,'und',0,'Building on a multi-year CLIP that included research showing the particular importance to African American male students of personal connections with faculty, the Village was created to provide a supportive setting for African American male students.  A collaboration between classified staff, faculty, and administrative employees, the Village is an intentional community led by elders who play key roles at all levels of the college. The Villagers are mentored by the elders and provided with a variety of workshops and support services.  ',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3800,8895,'und',0,'The intervention began in Engl 1301 (Composition) and was extended first to Hist 1301 and then Math 1314. For English and history, the intervention consists of assigned readings which are to be analyzed by the students outside of class and discussed in class. The math intervention consists of using a multi-step process for solving word problems. All faculty teaching these courses are now asked to implement the critical reading intervention.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3801,8896,'und',0,'The English Department\'s analysis of its former MP3-11 intervention data revealed a lower-than-expected rate of follow-on course-taking (English 91 to 101) among the target population.  These findings prompted the faculty to shift the ENGL 091 curriculum to a model of accelerated coursework where students literally co-enroll in the pre-college and college-level composition course. ','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3802,8897,'und',0,'Professional Development on student success strategies and pedagogy for targeted student groups has been an ATD intervention from the initial implementation of the ATD grant.  This past year alone, 417 faculty members attended 16 institutionally funded sessions sponsored by the Lee College Center for Teaching Excellence.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3803,8898,'und',0,'English faculty contracted with a consultant to perform a review of the writing curriculum and make recommendations for reform with the ultimate goal of greater student success and higher learning outcomes. This intervention was discussed in the previous report with an estimated start date of Fall 2011, however, the review and collaborative work required more time than expected. The resulting umbrella syllabus and resulting curriculum will be implemented in the fall of 2012.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3804,8899,'und',0,'Students enroll in two sequential 8-week developmental education courses in one subject. This allows students to complete two courses in one semester and provides daily instruction as compared to two per week in 15-week courses.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3805,8900,'und',0,'Additional in-class time was added to all developmental education courses.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3806,8901,'und',0,'For each level of the Developmental English and Developmental Reading courses, a theme from a college-level gateway course was selected and an integrated learning project around this theme was built with Reading, Writing, and Math skills integrated in this project. By contextualizing developmental courses within gateway course themes, the Dev. Reading and Dev. English programs aim at demonstrating to developmental students that what they learn in developmental courses has a meaningful connection to their college level courses and that reading, writing, and math skills are interrelated, too.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3807,8902,'und',0,'The Department of English applied faculty advising and Student Success SpecialistÕs advising in 10 pilot classes in Spring 2010. Starting from Fall 2010, the intervention strategies were modified to focus on time management and peer support group activities in the classroom. Instructors participating in the intervention project organize time management workshops, imbed time management strategies in the class assignments, and conduct weekly peer support group activities in the classroom. It is hoped that students who use time management skills will be able to come to class and complete class assignment on time, leading to successful completion of the course.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3808,8903,'und',0,'The Accelerated Learning Program (ALP) is for students who place into developmental English one level below the college level. Under the ALP model, students placed into upper-level developmental writing are mainstreamed into English 101 classes, and simultaneously enrolled in a companion ALP course (taught by the same instructor) that meets in the class period immediately following the English 101 class.  The aim of the ALP course, which has only eight students, is to help students maximize the likelihood of success in English 101.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3809,8904,'und',0,'An outgrowth of \"early alert,\" case management is a means of addressing the unique needs of developmental students.  Case managers are campus-based.  In addition to conducting multiple  workshops and arranging special activities for developmental students, the case manager\'s primary function is to serve as a  liaison between student and instructor and to help the student with individual educational plans for course success.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3810,8905,'und',0,'ENG 002 (Basic English 2) students who have no reading requirements are being given the opportunity to complete this upper-level developmental course while also taking ENG 111 with the same teacher.  Ten students from a designated ENG 002 class took ENG 111 last fall with 10 other students who were not developmental in English. Nine of these students earned a C or better in the ENG 111 class.  This semester two ENG 002 classes or 10 each are taking ENG 111 as well with ENG 111 students.  Demand for these Accelerated Learning Program (ALP) pairings is expected to grow as more and more students become aware of the opportunity to complete ENG 111 sooner.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3811,8906,'und',0,'The objective of this intervention is to make sure that the means of placing students in ENG 111 classes (SAT 510-540; ACT 18-20; Accuplacer 73 in Sentence Skills and 68 in Reading) are accurate.  These placement cut scores have been used for almost 12 years.  The performance in ENG 111 of 5 cohorts of students will be analyzed: 1.)  students with SAT 510-540 or ACT 18-20; 2.) students with relatively high scores on both the Accuplacer reading and sentence skills tests; 3.) students with middling scores on both the reading and sentence skills tests; 4.) students with high scores on the sentence skills test but relatively low scores on the reading test; and 5.) students with high scores on the reading tests but relatively low scores on the sentence skills test.  The data generated by this analysis will be used to adjust cut scores as needed.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3812,8907,'und',0,'Several steps have been or will be taken to better support part-time faculty (c. 40) who teach ENG 111 each academic year.  All part-time faculty teaching ENG 111 are currently given a 16-page standard syllabus on which to base their own syllabi as well as models of student papers that have been assessed by the Maryland C Standard.  Part-time ENG 111 faculty are also assigned mentors from among the full-time faculty.  A standing department committee, chaired by the supervisor of part-time faculty, reviews the instructional materials used by newly-hired part-time faculty and conducts class observations.  In response to requests received on a survey of the part-time faculty, several observations of full-time faculty have been scheduled for the part-time faculty.  Video clips of full-time faculty demonstrating best practices in their own classes are planned and will be made available to part-time colleagues.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3813,8908,'und',0,'Linking of college success course with English.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3814,8909,'und',0,'During the collegeÕs fourth implementation year of ATD, Brazosport College developed and implemented a new drop-in writing center.  A review of several indices of data indicated the need for this type of student support. This data includes success rates in developmental (i.e., transitional) English courses, responses from the Community College Student Survey of Engagement (CCSSE), and results from a recent faculty survey on current writing practices. \n\n\n\nPrior to the implementation of this initiative, there were only limited writing support services. As part of the ATD Initiative, a four-member faculty team began working during the third year of the ATD Initiative to develop this center. Specific outcomes to date include a review of best practice research, interviews with partnering ATD institutions, a faculty survey, and a presentation from a local writing center director and state representative for the Southwest Writing Center Association. In addition, the college is piloting a project that offers drop-in writing tutoring to students at the college. Thus far, the results are promising and indicate an increased utilization of writing services.\n\n',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3815,8910,'und',0,'This intervention was developed for First Time in College students placing into Developmental English. The Orientation goal is to expose students to the support services on campus, prepare them for the rigors of college and give them strategies to succeed. The orientation has three components. The first component is a student led PowerPoint overview of college services. The second component is a student life activity again led by students that enables students to form relationships with their peers. The last component is comprised of three 30 minute sessions that review the Academic Literacy I course, Counseling Services and Academic Support Services.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3816,8911,'und',0,'The Student Success Summit was a one day event in which students attending first and second year courses were assembled to participate in an interactive presentation by Mr. Erik Cork from International Write Now, Inc., a company that provides instruction in academic writing using a dynamic participatory format.  During this summit, students were engaged in a variety of hands-on writing activities.  International Write Now, Inc. uses a rap music format to engage students while providing them with hands-on techniques and tips to improve their academic writing skills.  ',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3817,8912,'und',0,'On Course training for faculty in gateway courses.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3818,8913,'und',0,'Mixed group study/instruction led by instructors and accompanied by food.  Offered on 2 out of 3 campuses.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3819,8914,'und',0,'Is a computer-assisted learning venue that formats math content into modules.  Students enroll in only those modules where they show a deficiency.  If students become proficient in the math modules they enrolled, they can enroll in the next developmental math course in the same semester.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3820,8915,'und',0,'Students that test and place into a developmental education course receive individualized advising which includes counseling on the proper courses registration, close monitoring of the proper prerequisites and of course attendance and completion.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3821,8916,'und',0,'Three types of tutoring have been phased in over the last two years: Tutoring for all developmental math classes as well as College Algebra; tutoring for developmental writing and Composition classes; online tutoring for Biology, Anatomy & Physiology, Composition, Intermediate and College Algebra. In the first three weeks of the semester, we run our Save Our Sanity program for new students to assist with computer-based skills (navigating email, ANGEL, and PeopleSoft).',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3822,8917,'und',0,'A compression strategy is used, compressing two semesters of developmental math into a single semester, using a combination of interactive videos and instructional software.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3823,8918,'und',0,'NC State offers a free 8-hour math refresher course prior to the start of each quarter. Students are targeted who fill within 11 points of the COMPASS cutoff score for college-level, as well as the top two developmental math courses. They are encouraged to attend the camp and retest on COMPASS immediately following the end of instruction. In addition to targeted scores, students with any score are welcome to attend and attempt to retest. This concept has since been expanded to the local high schools, with boot camps for seniors during spring at the high school sites co-taught by college and high school instructors. The college is continuing on-campus boot camps after the DEI grant through a fee for service arrangement.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3824,8919,'und',0,'The case management strategy involves both major policy/procedure changes, as well as technical investments through DEI funds. The major policy/procedure change has involved changing the structure of new student advising, including assignment of a dedicated advisor to students rather than ala carte service when the student arrives at the Success Center.  The new approach includes: breaks visits into: A. COMPASS testing/debrief; B. New Student Appointment with assigned advisor for pre-registration advising and completion of Education Plan; C. Final group session where students register for classes, receive schedule, orientation info, etc. The assigned advisor then keeps current with the student, including a required debrief for the Noel Levitz College Student Inventory taken by all developmental students in their FYE course. In addition, all advisors are now assigned students as part of their caseload in new student advising sessions, and maintain contact with these students until their promotion from the developmental advising program. These advisors maintain constant communication with other student support offices on individual student needs through the notes section of AdvisorTrac software.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3825,8920,'und',0,'All students in Pre-algebra and Introductory Algebra are required to complete online homework using the My Math Lab online courseware. Students are encouraged to utilize the tutorials, videos, and animations provided in the online resource to increase engagement and strengthen comprehension of critical course concepts.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3826,8921,'und',0,'Reduced section size from 35 to 24 students, shifted to Accuplacer, created Pre-Algebra (enrolls about 30% of the developmental math students), aligned developmental math course outlines, and instructional changes in Fall 2010 included new text book, project-based approach & common final.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3827,8922,'und',0,'Establish a college level math lab which will provide tutoring, computerized assistance, instructional technology resources, study groups, workshops, and other instructional support services.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3828,8923,'und',0,'Pilot a supplemental instruction model for one section of Basic Algebra II and one section of College Algebra. This initial goal has been expanded to other math courses and other disciplines.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3829,8924,'und',0,'All developmental math courses were converted to 8-week courses with multiple modes of instruction.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3830,8925,'und',0,'Reviewed and revised intermediate algebra (IA) curriculum as it relates forward to college algebra (CA) outcomes.  Review also prompted mapping backward to basic algebra and basic math (prerequisites to IA) and the development of a common final exam for CA.  Work plan includes observing IA retention and CA success rates to monitor effects of curriculum mapping.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3831,8926,'und',0,'This interventions was developed for academically underprepared, pell grant recipients, first-generation in college students. The College paired a beginning Algebra course with a Self-Improvement, tutor - embedded course.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3832,8927,'und',0,'MyMathLab - competency-based, computer-assisted program, requiring mandatory attendance. A facilitator is available for assistance and explanations. From student feedback and faculty observations, initiative leaders determined to add a brief lecture, and this has helped the pass rate.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3833,8928,'und',0,'This intervention was developed to address the needs of all developmental math students (500 per semester). A complete revision of the developmental math curriculum was undertaken with the addition of computer-aided instruction (MyMathLab) at all three DE levels (to now include college algebra).  Additional contact hours were added to each course, and a developmental math lab was created with staffing by math faculty.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3834,8929,'und',0,'The Math Path offers welcoming, supportive, faculty and peer facilitated developmental math study sessions that encourage students to spend more time on task, a major predictor of math success. In the Math Path, at least one faculty member is present and works together student peer tutors to foster and model successful math learning',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3835,8930,'und',0,'The Yearlong Algebra cohort is a committed cohort of students recruited specifically for this intervention , who begin  in Fall with Algebra I (Math 084) continue through Algebra II (Math 085) in winter, and complete gatekeeper Intermediate Algebra (Math 098) in spring. It addresses the high rates of attrition seen over the course of the developmental math sequence. The intention is to provide a supportive learning environment for students who have faced barriers to success in math, including a history of being unsuccessful in learning math, and lack of study skills. Students are recruited based on low placement scores and through referrals from counselors. As a condition of joining the cohort, must get permission from the instructor, and sign a contract stating their intention to complete the course sequence, to fully participate in the class, complete their homework assignments and submit them on time, and to use the Math Path.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3836,8931,'und',0,'This program links intermediate algebra with college algebra by enabling students to complete both in one semester using a revised curriculum and additional academic support.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3837,8932,'und',0,'Due to an unscalable advising intervention, a shift occurred in year 3 of the grant to pre-college math curriculum reform. Now fully implemented, this curricular overhaul has eliminated one full level within the pre-college math curriculum, shrinking the remediation pathway by one academic term for most students. At the same time, the faculty has revised the contents of the pre-college courses, with the goal of increasing their relevance, application, and interest.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3838,8933,'und',0,'This intervention revised the intermediate algebra curriculum of the old Math 99 Intermediate Algebra (for STEM majors) and the curriculum of the old Math 097 Intermediate Algebra (for the Liberal Arts). The new courses are Math 096 Introduction to Pre Calculus (for STEM majors) and Math 095 Intermediate Algebra (for non-STEM majors).  This change also focused on students enrolling in the correct course.  Prior to the change 483/2181 = 22% of the intermediate algebra students enrolled in non-STEM bound intermediate algebra (Math 097) verses after the change 2133/2966 = 72% now take the non-STEM bound intermediate algebra (Math 095). ',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3839,8934,'und',0,'All Math Study Skills(MARC) classes are 2-credits.  MARC courses are linked to a specific developmental math class Ð Arithmetic, Introduction to Elementary Algebra, Elementary Algebra, Intermediate Algebra.  Topics include math study skills, reading a math textbook, overcoming math and test anxiety, learning style evaluation, test taking skills and stress management.    ',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3840,8935,'und',0,'Statistics tutoring lab',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3841,8936,'und',0,'Students in SI sections meet several times per week in a \"study\" session outside of class time with a peer tutor who also attends the course each class meeting. Peer tutors have already completed the course successfully and are selected by faculty.','','plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3842,8937,'und',0,'Design and implement processes and interventions to enhance student achievement and change college policies to enforce student participation in ATD activities.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3843,8938,'und',0,'The math curriculum has been extensively revised over time to allow two pathways through developmental math, one for liberal arts majors, and a modularized computer assisted course to prepare students to enter the algebra sequence.',NULL,'plain_text');
INSERT INTO `field_data_body` VALUES ('node','intervention',0,3844,8939,'und',0,'Developed for at-risk mathematics students,  Lecture/lab options are presented to students.  Modular mathematics is being developed for developmental students.  A second initiative in this area involves implementing a modular math format for all three levels of mathematics.',NULL,'plain_text');
